RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIT KAT KIDD stalked the pace from three wide down the backstretch then moved out to four wide into upper for a rally and drew clear late. FLASH FREDDIE was off the pace in the two path then moved out to three wide at the quarter pole for a bid, drove past the leaders to take a brief lead but was ran down in late stretch by the outside rival to be second best. RAZZ raced near the back on the backstretch then circled the field around the turn and made a late rally to be up for the show. THA ILLEST DEAL sprinted away to co-lead to the quarter pole then took a brief lead through the turn but weakened in the stretch. PETEY saved ground while racing in the middle of the pack through the turn then tipped out to three wide in the stretch to improve his position. STRAY CAT STRUT trailed the filed while saving ground through the turn and passed tired rivals in the stretch. REGINALD AURELIUS hustled to the front to co-lead to the quarter pole and faded. ST JOE chased the leaders down the backstretch, saved ground around the turn but failed to menace and was vanned off. CHECKULATER raced off the pace from four wide to the three furlong marker and retreated. KNIGHT OF HONOR was forwardly placed on the inside to the eighth pole and gave way.

ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, saved ground, passed tiring rivals,

COAL DANCER tracked the leaders down the backstretch from two wide then moved out to three wide on the final turn going along side PLUM WINE into the stretch but couldn't continue to match strides but proved second best. BELLAMYSAWESOMEDAY raced off the pace while saving ground around the first turn then made a mild bid on the backstretch and flattened out. TIFFANY'S FERRARI went to the front to set the pace for a half but was over taken going into the stretch and tired. STEEL GUITAR pressed the pace from the two path to the final turn and weakened. COZY COURTNEY stalked the pace from three wide to the half mile marker and retreated. C C LLAM was allowed to settled at the back but never made a bid.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOPESHECANRUN roused to the front to take a pressured lead to the top of the stretch then drew clear proving best. CHIPEEE was shuffled back after the break then steadily advanced through the turn, moved out to seven wide for a late rally. TRUVY'S BANDIT raced off the pace to the turn then made a three wide bid on the turn and engaged the leaders at the top of the stretch but was no match for the top two and held the show. LITTLE WARRIOR trailed the field early, saved ground around the turn then moved out to five wide going into the stretch to make a late run to improve position. COUNTRY CAT JAKE pressed the pace from the inside but lacked the late response needed. I'M A NIGHT TRAIN raced off the pace from four wide through the turn but was empty in the stretch. BELLAMY BROTHER broke in slightly at the start and bumped inside rival, settled in the middle of the pack to mid turn then moved between horses at the three sixteenths pole but faltered. FLASH OF RAIN went to a brief early lead then vied for the lead from two wide to the top of the stretch and tired. BOSS MAN ZONG raced near the back and was not a threat. FISHIN WITH PETE was bumped then veered out after the break, settled in the middle of the pack early and was never a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOD'S GOLD was roused to the front to set the pace and take a clear lead into the first turn, held that position through the final turn then drew off. SOULOLOGY saved ground to the final turn the moved out to the two path to make a mild bid to improve position. AWESOME CAJUN was away alertly then settled on the inside to save ground to no avail. RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 5 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Condition E ligibility Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEYOND THE HYPE went to the front to an unchallenged lead and held that position while keeping to task in the stretch. SENSE OF FLURRY was off the pace in the two path made a bid on the turn but couldn't catch the winner but held on for the place. CAJUN ACES stalked the pace from the two path down the backstretch then made a three wide bid at the eighth pole, bumped with MIDNIGHT TRIP before making a late run and missed the place. MSCHITCHATTOUR trailed around the first turn then moved up from four wide through the final turn and showed late interest. MIDNIGHT TRIP raced in the middle of the pack on the first turn then moved up from three wide through the final turn but was bumped by CAJUN ACES in upper stretch and was empty in the drive. LOVIN LIVIN tracked the leaders from the two path to the top of the stretch and weakened. KELLYS THE BOSS was allowed to settle down the backstretch then moved up for three of four wide on the final turn for a mild rally. US SECOND CUTE PIE showed little. GLORY TO ME saved ground to no avail. BARRANCA was off the pace on the inside for a half and retreated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PLENTY OF CENTS tracked the leaders down the backstretch, moved between horses at the five sixteenths pole to engage the leader, took the lead at the eighth pole and held on for the win. NAPOLEONIC CODE raced five wide into the first turn then was forwardly placed while racing four wide down the backstretch then made a bid midway through the final turn but couldn't catch the winner but proved to be second best. OUT MAKING TREBLE was allowed to settled down the backstretch then moved between horses at the three furlong marker, tipped in to make a rail bid on the final turn, had to move out to the two path in the stretch and was up of the show. ROLL ON OUT went to the lead from the inside down the backstretch then was challenged at the quarter pole, matched strides with outside rival around the final turn and gave way grudgingly. CAPTAINS COVE was unhurried around the first turn then moved up down the backstretch and made a looming bid on the final turn but faltered. JESUIT trailed the field around the first turn then made a mild bid from three wide on the backstretch and passed tiring rivals. HAIL THE CAT rushed away from the gate and vied for the lead from the two path to the three furlong maker and gave way. MORO FLYBOY raced off the pace from three wide to the three furlong marker then dropped back, bled and was vanned off. F J'S FLACO tracked leaders from the inside around the first turn and dropped back. GTUONE BUCK remained back.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 8 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Allowance Purse 36000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 22 Allowed 4 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LACIE BE GOOD went to the front to set all the pace, was challenged entering the backstretch but came again and drew off to prove best. RAIN roused to the front to press the pace down the backstretch and fell back on the turn but dug in in late stretch to save the place. MISS LONELYHEARTS raced off the pace from the two path down the backstretch then saved ground around the final turn and fought gamely in the stretch but was outfinished late. WESTERN DREAM was off the pace down the backstretch but fell back on the final turn and came again to be best of the rest. FORGOTTEN FORTUNE raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch, moved up from the two path on the final turn for a late run but was outkicked in the stretch. CZAR'S BALLERINA raced near the back around the first turn advance from four wide at the three furlong maker to improve her position. ROSES ARE GRAY raced in the middle of the pack, moved between horses at the five sixteenths pole to make a bid on the leaders at the top of the stretch but hung. PAINTBRUSH was never a threat. ROLL GYPSY ROLL saved ground while racing in the middle of the pack to the final turn and faded. PUGLIA was unhurried and never fired.
